author: rec
msg: [UIMA-2808] - JCasUtil Subiterator returns annotations which are not within borders of the container (parent) annotation if parameter "strict" is set to "false"

- Unambigous subiterator was always returning first annotation of index type due to missing boundary check. Changed logic to void pre-fetching "current" annotation and avoid overlap check with "current" annotation while it's not set yet.
